Package squidpony.squidgrid

Class GridData

java.lang.Object
squidpony.squidgrid.GridData
public class GridData
extends Object
Customized storage of multiple types of 2D data, accessible by String (or CharSequence) keys. Meant for cases where SquidLib needs to produce a grid with multiple types of data, such as what could be represented by a 2D array of objects containing only char, int, double, and/or float data, but this is much more memory-efficient than producing many objects. This can be seen as a "struct-of-array" approach, to use C terminology, rather than an "array-of-struct" approach. This also allows new 2D arrays to be added to an existing GridData if needed.
